JSON  Overview

JSON  

JSON stands for JavaScript Object Notation.

It is a lightweight text-based open standard designed for human-readable data interchange. Its light weight alternative to XML for exchanging data on the network.

Conventions used by JSON are known to programmers which include C, C++, Java, Python, Perl etc.

  
This format was specified by Douglas Crockford. This was designed for human-readable data interchange 

Extended from the JavaScript scripting language.

The filename extension is .json

JSON Internet Media type is application/json 

Uses of JSON

1. Used in  JavaScript based application which includes websites development. 

2. JSON format is used for serializing & transmitting structured data over network connection. 

3. This is primarily used to transmit data between server and client application. 

4. Web Services use JSON format to provide public data.

5. It can be used with modern programming languages.

Java JSON

Support exists in different varieties

1. Jackson json library -- JAR
2. Google GSon
3. Json.simple










